payment /ˈpeɪmənt/

(payments) 

1. N-COUNT A payment is an amount of money that is paid to someone, or the act of paying this money. 支付的款项; 支付 

2. N-UNCOUNT Payment is the act of paying money to someone or of being paid. 支付 

例： He had sought to obtain payment of a sum which he had claimed was owed to him. 他曾试图获得一笔他声称是欠他的钱。 

3.  →  see also balance of payments , down payment

